  "local_port": 48674,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "Setting a default font in Gmail ensures that every time you compose a new email, your chosen font style, size, and color are automatically applied. Here\u2019s how you can set up your default font in Gmail:\n\n### **Step-by-Step Guide to Set a Default Font in Gmail**\n\n1. **Open Gmail:**\n   - Go to [Gmail](https://mail.google.com/) and log in to your account if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Access Gmail Settings:**\n   - In the top right corner of Gmail, click on the **gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f)** to open the Quick Settings panel.\n   \n3. **Navigate to All Settings:**\n   - Within the Quick Settings panel, click on **\"See all settings\"** to open the full settings menu.\n\n4. **Locate the \"Default Text Style\" Section:**\n   - By default, you'll land on the **\"General\"** tab.\n   - Scroll down until you find the **\"Default text style\"** section.\n\n5. **Set Your Preferred Font Style:**\n   - Here, you can customize the **Font**, **Size**, **Text color**, and **Default formatting options (Bold, Italic, Underline)**.\n   - Click on each option to select your preferred settings. For example:\n     - **Font:** Choose from options like Arial, Calibri, Times New Roman, etc.\n     - **Size:** Select the desired text size.\n     - **Color:** Pick a text color that suits your preference.\n   \n   ![Gmail Default Text Style](https://i.imgur.com/YourImageLink.png)\n   \n6. **Scroll Down and Save Changes:**\n   - After customizing your default text style, scroll to the bottom of the settings page.\n   - Click on the **\"Save Changes\"** button to apply your new default font settings.\n\n7. **Compose a New Email to Verify:**\n   - Click on the **\"Compose\"** button to start a new email.\n   - Your selected default font settings should automatically appear in the email body area.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Rich Formatting:** Ensure that **Rich formatting** is enabled when composing emails to utilize the customized fonts and styles. You can toggle this option at the bottom of the compose window.\n  \n- **Resetting to Defaults:** If you ever wish to revert to Gmail\u2019s default font settings, go back to the **\"Default text style\"** section and manually select Gmail's original settings or use the **\"Reset\"** option if available.\n\n- **Browser Compatibility:** Make sure you're using a supported web browser and that it's updated to the latest version to ensure all Gmail features work correctly.\n\n- **No Impact on Received Emails:** Setting a default font only affects the emails you **compose** and **send**. It does not change the appearance of emails you receive.\n\nBy following these steps, you can personalize your email composition experience in Gmail, making your messages look consistent and tailored to your preferences.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or the interface looks different, it might be due to updates in Gmail\u2019s interface. In such cases, refer to Gmail's [Help Center](https://support.google.com/mail/) for the most recent instructions.",
